CM ============================================================
CM Arcanum Reference Deck — Axial-Mode Helix Over Ground Plane
CM V-REAL-003 in docs/nec-import/validation.md
CM ============================================================
CM 5-turn axial-mode helix over PEC ground plane.
CM This is ORI's primary use case — ground station helix antenna
CM for satellite communication.
CM
CM This deck exercises the full CMoM advantage:
CM   - GH card (helix geometry) exercises curved-segment parsing
CM   - GN card (PEC ground) exercises Phase 1 image generation
CM   - The helix is precisely where CMoM outperforms NEC-2
CM
CM Geometry:
CM   Frequency:      300 MHz  (lambda = 1.0 m)
CM   Turns:          5
CM   Circumference:  1.0 m    (C = lambda, axial mode condition)
CM   Radius:         C/(2*pi) = 0.15915 m
CM   Pitch (S):      0.25 m   (S = lambda/4, typical axial mode)
CM   Total length:   5 * 0.25 = 1.25 m
CM   Wire radius:    0.001 m
CM   Segments:       40 total (8 per turn)
CM   Helix axis:     z-axis, starting at z = 0 (ground plane)
CM
CM Axial mode condition: 0.75 < C/lambda < 1.33
CM   C/lambda = 1.0 — center of axial mode range. Good.
CM
CM Source:
CM   Delta-gap at helix feed (tag 1, segment 1)
CM   Feed point is at z = 0, on the ground plane
CM
CM Expected results (Kraus approximations, Phase 4 V-HEL-001):
CM   Gain:  G ≈ 6.2 * N * (C/lambda)^2 * (S/lambda)
CM        = 6.2 * 5 * 1.0 * 0.25 = 7.75 ≈ 8.9 dBi
CM   HPBW:  ≈ 52 / sqrt(N * C/lambda) = 52 / sqrt(5) ≈ 23 degrees
CM   Z_in:  ≈ 140 * (C/lambda) = 140 Ω (resistive, near-resonant)
CM   Polarization: right-hand circular (RHCP)
CM   Axial ratio: AR ≈ 1 over main beam
CM
CM Tolerance: Arcanum result should be within 20-30% of Kraus values.
CM   Kraus formulas are engineering approximations, not exact.
CM   See phase4-postprocessing/validation.md V-HEL-001 for
CM   pass/fail criteria.
CM
CM Ground plane:
CM   GN 1 = PEC ground plane
CM   GE 1 = geometry end with ground plane flag
CM   Phase 1 will generate image segments (40 additional segments)
CM   Total segments after image generation: 80
CM
CM CMoM vs NEC-2 comparison:
CM   This deck is also used for V-HEL-002 (CMoM vs polygon).
CM   Run once with Arcanum CMoM (default), once with straight-segment
CM   approximation, and compare against high-N reference solution.
CM   CMoM must outperform straight segments at 8 segments/turn.
CM
CM Provenance: Synthesized by ORI for Arcanum validation.
CM   Parameters chosen to match axial mode conditions exactly.
CM   Ground plane configuration matches ORI ground station use case.
CM   Kraus formulas from: Kraus, J.D., Antennas, Chapter 7.
CE
CM ============================================================
CM GEOMETRY
CM ============================================================
CM Tag 1: 5-turn axial-mode helix
CM   GH format: tag, segments, pitch(m), total_length(m),
CM              radius_start(m), radius_end(m), wire_radius(m)
CM   Uniform helix: radius_start = radius_end = 0.15915 m
GH 1 40 0.25 1.25 0.15915 0.15915 0.001
CM
CM PEC ground plane at z = 0
CM Phase 1 will reflect helix segments through z = 0
GN 1
GE 1
CM ============================================================
CM SIMULATION PARAMETERS
CM ============================================================
CM Delta-gap voltage source at helix feed (tag 1, segment 1)
EX 0 1 1 0 1.0 0.0
CM
CM Frequency: 300 MHz
FR 0 1 0 0 299.792458 0.0
CM
CM Frequency sweep near design frequency (uncomment to use)
CM FR 0 11 0 0 250.0 10.0
CM
CM Far-field pattern, upper hemisphere only (ground plane present)
CM theta: 0 to 90 degrees (upper hemisphere), 5 degree steps
CM phi:   0 to 360 degrees, 5 degree steps
RP 0 19 73 1000 0.0 0.0 5.0 5.0 0.0
CM
EN
